org.nerd4j.csv.field.converter

Class AbstractCSVFieldConverter<S,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.nerd4j.csv.field.converter.AbstractCSVFieldConverter<S,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - type of the source field format.
    T - type of the target field format.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CSVProcessOperation, CSVFieldConverter<S,T>, CSVRegistryEntry
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BooleanToString, DateToString, EnumToString, NumberToString, StringToBoolean, StringToDate, StringToEnum, StringToNumber

    public abstract class AbstractCSVFieldConverter<S,T>
extends Object
implements CSVFieldConverter<S,T>
    Abstract implementation of the CSVFieldConverter interface that performs the expected behavior and modifies the CSVFieldProcessContext accordingly with the framework execution policy.

    Any custom implementation of the CSVFieldConverter interface should extend this class.

    Author:
    Nerd4j Team

      • getErrorMessagePattern

        public String getErrorMessagePattern()
        Returns a message pattern as described in the MessageFormat class.

        The placeholders in this pattern coincide with fields of the CSVFieldProcessContext as follows:

        • {0} = columnName;
        • {1} = originalValue;
        • {2} = convertedValue.
        Specified by:
        getErrorMessagePattern in interface CSVProcessOperation
        Returns:
        the pattern to use to build the error message.

      • convert

        public T convert(S source,
                 CSVFieldProcessContext context)
        Applies the conversion of the field in source format and returns the field in target format.

        If the conversion fails it modifies the context accordingly with the framework policies.

        Specified by:
        convert in interface CSVFieldConverter<S,T>
        Parameters:
        source - the CSV field to convert.
        context - the field process execution context.
        Returns:
        the CSV field in converted format.
